y you on your pesonal website. With Message boards on either EZ boards or another message board service.  This board service here has decent capabilities and compared to EZ board's the later just plain sucks.<BR> Find out from yu current hosts what the costs of remaining pop-up free would be. Them damn popups stack and stack eating up CPU processing power in amazing chunks, imagine the bandwidth and frame load from half a dozen animated and active X banners. Who's to prevent hooked banners...those are banner's who add in hooks into your processes and reoccur when you change pages even though you aren't on the source page anymore and they cache and cookie exchange your moves while active and your bowsr is up. Kinda invasive. <BR> Then there are the pop-up banners that are linked to the page itself, close the banner or pop-up add and the page's contents go BLANK...yep. Gotta keep it up to view...kinda like electronic torture and blackmail all in one.  PURE PITA (pain in the A**). Not to mention Cycle eating sumbiotches on your kernel's cycles.<BR> I've stopped going to certain websites where I've found that type of content, it's been only purgable with a full reboot. And some make my firewall go nuts.<BR> I think the pop-up adds with kel hooking capabilities are intrusive and a security risk.<P> back to the subject at hand- (it's late forgive me ehhh?)<P>  Site's with a history, and a contract you can ue as legal recourse are best.<P> I think EZ board's will still suffer as the internet restructures.<P> So home based hosted might be good- but then  you might not be able to play both your SK and Cleric same time neh?<P> I'm nearly done with EQ myself. Shadow's of Lucin is window dressing.<BR> I'm looking forward to SWOL and SB right now.<BR> And writing more. Screenwriter's strike coming up is going to kill me if it's longer than 3 months. Hopefully I can sell a few stories meanwhile and or a novel.<P> That's me 2 cents, and then some.<P>Brodder<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR